OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1780052575
OL,3,CStepmother killed girl in scalding
OL,4,Cbath in 1978, jury finds
OL,6,FAsked whether Nix said anything, Mr
OL,7,FBernard replied: "She asked me to say
OL,8,Fit was an accident... and to say that
OL,9,Fwe were in the garden when it happened
OL,10,Fand that she would never beat me
OL,11,Fagain."
OL,13,FAsked what he did, he said: "I lied, I
OL,14,Ftold everyone that story."
OL,16,FAsked why, Mr Bernard replied:
OL,17,F"Because I didn't feel protected, I
OL,18,Fjust wanted it to stop."
OL,26,@oD@ROUsD@GO]uD@]OUvD@ZO]yD@AOUzD@XO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/16
